{%- comment -%}
  Flyout Menu
  File: snippets/flyout-menu.liquid

  Sidebar-style "browse all categories" flyout block — left-hand list of
  top-level categories, right-hand content panel that swaps per category,
  rendered for the 'flyout' block type in sections/header-menu.liquid.

  Pairs with:
    assets/flyout-menu.css
    assets/flyout-menu.js

  Usage (from sections/header-menu.liquid):
    {%- when 'flyout' -%}
      {%- render 'flyout-menu', block: block -%}

  Accepts:
    block - the flyout block, with settings: menu, link, label, icon, panel_style

  ── LEVEL MAPPING ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
  L1 (flyout_menu.links)   → left sidebar categories
                              e.g. "Electric Scooters"
                              rendered as .flyout-panel__category-link

  L2 (link.links)          → one .flyout-panel__column PER L2 link,
                              laid out as a horizontal row of columns
                              (see assets/flyout-menu.css). Each column's
                              heading is e.g. "Trending", "Shop by
                              Category", "Shop by Price", rendered as
                              .flyout-panel__group.

  L3 (sublink.links)       → indented sub-links stacked vertically
                              under each L2 heading, e.g. "Shop all",
                              "New arrivals", "On sale", rendered as
                              .flyout-panel__sublink
  ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  Current-page awareness: `flyout_active_index` finds the top-level link
  whose branch contains the page the visitor is currently on (via
  Shopify's `link.active`, which is true for the link itself OR any of
  its descendants) and pre-selects that category + panel instead of
  always defaulting to the first one. Falls back to the first category
  when nothing in the menu matches the current page (e.g. visitor is on
  the homepage).

  Column layout: every L2 link under the active L1 category becomes its
  own .flyout-panel__column — there is no longer a fixed "2 buckets"
  split. assets/flyout-menu.css lays these columns out as a horizontal,
  wrapping row (CSS flexbox, not a fixed-count grid), so the number of
  columns rendered always matches the number of L2 links exactly, no
  matter how many a merchant adds. The "All {{ link.title }}" link is
  rendered once, after the columns row, as its own element — it is no
  longer nested inside whichever bucket happened to be "last".

  Promo image support intentionally not included — see prior removal.

  CHANGELOG (this revision):
  - CHANGED (breaking layout change): removed the old "split L2 groups
    into 2 vertical buckets" logic (col1_limit / col2_limit / the
    `for col in (0..1)` loop with offset/limit). That approach forced
    every category into exactly 2 vertical stacks regardless of how
    many L2 groups it had, which is not what was wanted — L2 groups
    should each be their own column, displayed as a horizontal list.
    Replaced with a single `for sublink in sub_links` loop that emits
    one .flyout-panel__column per L2 link, in source order, with no
    bucketing/splitting math at all.
  - MOVED: the "All {{ link.title }}" link used to be appended inside
    whichever column was rendered last (column index 1). Since there is
    no longer a fixed "last column," it's now rendered once, as a
    sibling after .flyout-panel__columns, so it always appears as a
    single panel-level link regardless of how many L2 columns exist.
  - REMOVED: `col1_limit` / `col2_limit` assigns and the `(0..1)` column
    loop — no longer needed now that columns map 1:1 to L2 links.
  - NOTE: pairs with the matching assets/flyout-menu.css rewrite, which
    switches `.flyout-panel__columns` from a fixed-count CSS grid to a
    wrapping flexbox row. The two files must be updated together — this
    Liquid change alone, without the matching CSS, would still render
    correctly (columns would just stack vertically using flex default),
    but you want both for the horizontal layout.
  - ADDED (earlier revision, unchanged here): "Flyout panel style" block
    setting (`panel_style`), giving merchants a Compact / Full-width
    span choice in the theme editor. `flyout_panel_classes` appends
    `flyout-panel--full-width` to the panel's class list when
    `block.settings.panel_style == 'full-width'`. Defaults to compact
    when the setting is blank/unset.
{%- endcomment -%}

{%- assign flyout_menu = linklists[block.settings.menu] -%}

{%- if flyout_menu != blank and flyout_menu.links.size > 0 -%}
  {%- assign flyout_active_index = 0 -%}
  {%- for link in flyout_menu.links -%}
    {%- if link.active and flyout_active_index == 0 -%}
      {%- assign flyout_active_index = forloop.index -%}
    {%- endif -%}
  {%- endfor -%}
  {%- if flyout_active_index == 0 -%}
    {%- assign flyout_active_index = 1 -%}
  {%- endif -%}
{%- endif -%}

{%- comment -%}
  Panel style: "compact" (default) keeps the existing left-aligned
  sidebar look. "full-width" appends the modifier class that
  assets/flyout-menu.css uses to span the panel across the header.
{%- endcomment -%}
{%- assign flyout_panel_classes = 'flyout-panel' -%}
{%- if block.settings.panel_style == 'full-width' -%}
  {%- assign flyout_panel_classes = flyout_panel_classes | append: ' flyout-panel--full-width' -%}
{%- endif -%}

<li class="menu-bar__item menu-bar__item--has-flyout" {{ block.shopify_attributes }}>
  <a href="{{ block.settings.link | default: flyout_menu.links.first.url | default: '#' }}"
     class="menu-bar__link menu-bar__link--caret flyout-trigger"
     aria-haspopup="true"
     aria-expanded="false"
     aria-controls="flyout-panel-{{ block.id }}"
     data-flyout-trigger>
    {%- if block.settings.icon != blank -%}
      <span class="menu-bar__icon">{%- render 'menu-icon', icon: block.settings.icon -%}</span>
    {%- endif -%}
    {{ block.settings.label | default: 'Browse all categories' }}
    <svg class="icon-caret-down" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="none" aria-hidden="true">
      <path d="M16.25 7.5L10 13.75L3.75 7.5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
    </svg>
  </a>

  {%- if flyout_menu != blank and flyout_menu.links.size > 0 -%}
    <div class="{{ flyout_panel_classes }}"
         id="flyout-panel-{{ block.id }}"
         role="region"
         aria-label="{{ block.settings.label | default: 'Browse all categories' }}"
         data-flyout-panel>
      <div class="flyout-panel__container">

        {%- comment -%} ── L1: sidebar categories ── {%- endcomment -%}
        <ul class="flyout-panel__categories" role="list">
          {%- for link in flyout_menu.links -%}
            {%- assign panel_id = 'flyout-panel-' | append: block.id | append: '-' | append: forloop.index -%}
            <li class="flyout-panel__category{% if forloop.index == flyout_active_index %} is-active{% endif %}">
              <a href="{{ link.url }}"
                 class="flyout-panel__category-link"
                 data-flyout-category-trigger
                 data-flyout-target="{{ panel_id }}"
                 aria-controls="{{ panel_id }}"
                 {% if link.current %}aria-current="page"{% endif %}>
                {{ link.title }}
                <svg class="icon-caret-right" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="none" aria-hidden="true">
                  <path d="M7.5 3.75L13.75 10L7.5 16.25" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
                </svg>
              </a>
            </li>
          {%- endfor -%}
        </ul>

        <div class="flyout-panel__content" data-flyout-content>
          {%- for link in flyout_menu.links -%}
            {%- assign panel_id = 'flyout-panel-' | append: block.id | append: '-' | append: forloop.index -%}
            {%- assign sub_links = link.links -%}

            <div class="flyout-panel__panel{% if forloop.index == flyout_active_index %} is-active{% endif %}"
                 id="{{ panel_id }}"
                 role="region"
                 aria-hidden="{% if forloop.index == flyout_active_index %}false{% else %}true{% endif %}"
                 data-flyout-panel-item>

              {%- comment -%}
                One .flyout-panel__column PER L2 link — no bucketing.
                assets/flyout-menu.css lays these out as a horizontal,
                wrapping row, so the rendered column count always
                matches sub_links.size exactly.
              {%- endcomment -%}
              <div class="flyout-panel__columns">
                {%- for sublink in sub_links -%}
                  <div class="flyout-panel__column">
                    {%- comment -%} L2: bold group heading (e.g. "Trending") {%- endcomment -%}
                    <a href="{{ sublink.url }}"
                       class="flyout-panel__group"
                       {% if sublink.current %}aria-current="page"{% endif %}>
                      {{ sublink.title }}
                    </a>
                    {%- if sublink.links.size > 0 -%}
                      {%- comment -%} L3: indented sub-links under this heading (e.g. "Shop all", "New arrivals", "On sale") {%- endcomment -%}
                      <ul class="flyout-panel__sublist" role="list">
                        {%- for grandchild in sublink.links -%}
                          <li>
                            <a href="{{ grandchild.url }}"
                               class="flyout-panel__sublink"
                               {% if grandchild.current %}aria-current="page"{% endif %}>
                              {{ grandchild.title }}
                            </a>
                          </li>
                        {%- endfor -%}
                      </ul>
                    {%- endif -%}
                  </div>
                {%- endfor -%}
              </div>

              {%- comment -%}
                Rendered once per panel now (not nested inside a
                column), since there's no longer a fixed "last column"
                to attach it to.
              {%- endcomment -%}
              <a href="{{ link.url }}" class="flyout-panel__all-link">
                All {{ link.title }}
                <svg class="icon-arrow-right" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="none" aria-hidden="true">
                  <path d="M4 10H16M16 10L11 5M16 10L11 15" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
                </svg>
              </a>

            </div>
          {%- endfor -%}
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  {%- endif -%}
</li>